menu "SC Bridge / GameLink"

    config SC_BRIDGE_ENABLED
        bool "Enable SC-Bridge network connection and GameLink event dispatcher"
        default n
        help
            When enabled the firmware will:
              - Start sc_network (Wi-Fi + WebSocket client) to connect to the
                PC-side sc-bridge daemon.
              - Start sc_gamelink to receive and dispatch game-state events
                (gear, shields, quantum drive, etc.) over that connection.
              - Show the Pairing screen on first boot until a bridge host is
                configured.

            Disable this option when the hardware is being used as a standalone
            HID controller without a running sc-bridge instance on the PC.
            The USB HID, LVGL UI, and SD-card ship layouts continue to work
            normally; only real-time game-state feedback is suppressed.

endmenu
